title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 4 data points.
Overall Share of respondents has increased over the Year
Share of respondents is rapidly increasing from 65+_years to 50-64_years, roughly constant from 50-64_years to 30-49_years, and lastly rapidly increasing from 30-49_years to 18-29_years.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 30-49_years and 18-29_years.
Max Share of respondents about 22.0 was recorded at Year 18-29_years
Min Share of respondents about 3.0 was recorded at Year 65+_years
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 4 data points. The chart has 2 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 65+_years to 30-49_years.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is slightly increasing which exists from 30-49_years to 18-29_years.
